The paper proposes an alternative way to implement the Analog Ensemble (AnEn) method using deep generative models. This involves reducing the amount of memory required to produce the probabilistic forecast by several orders of magnitude and generating a meaningful set of analogs associated with a certain forecast in constant time without performing any search. This work involves machine learning and deep learning techniques, which are typically associated with the computer science sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.SD (Software Engineering). Additionally, the paper involves statistical modeling and data analysis, which are associated with the sub-categories of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
